    "For instance, in [9], the authors present a comprehensive review of Indoor-HAR, an emerging technology leveraging cameras and vision-based sensors to assess human actions within indoor settings.",
    "The review encompasses contemporary approaches, existing challenges, practical implementations, dataset resources, and a proposed taxonomy for Indoor-HAR.",
    "The study also highlights the potential of this technology in various industries, such as healthcare, surveillance, and human-computer interaction.",
    "It has multiple applications in smart homes, elderly care, and assisted living.",
    "Debnath et al., [10] investigated different computer vision approaches for physical rehabilitation and assessment."
